	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=1511&mid=104939961179620>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=1511&mid=104939961179620>RE: Auto Chain Casting?</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=1511&mid=104939961179620#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Apr 3rd 3:29 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2440><span id=Sage>Dargadin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>950 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I don't think you can build hotkeys that use other hotkeys.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you could, it would be possible to make key 1 perform key 2 five times, and key 2 perform key 3 five times, etc, so that you would eventually be able to program 5^9 (nearly 2 million) instances of key number 10 (or 0).<br><br>So, if key #0 was set to &quot;/gsay &lt;in some foreign language&gt; something&quot;, you could in theory hit key 1 and spam your group 2 million times, thus maxing out their language (or at least bringing it up one higher than your own).  Also, if key #2 said do key #3, and key #3 said do key #2, hitting either key would throw you into an infinite loop.<br><br>For these reasons, SOE doesn't let you use hotkeys within hotkeys.</p>&nbsp;<br>______________________________________<br><b>Dargadin, Barbarian Shaman of the 61st Season</b><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=494767" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=494767</a><br><b><span style='color: red;'>Lost Fires</span style='color: red;'><br>Ayonae Ro Server</b><br></td></tr>
